    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "so you're saying that simply adding an `fsync=True` kwarg that causes close to be:\n\n``` python\nf_fd = store._handle.fileno()\nstore.flush()\nos.fsync(f_fd)\nstore.close()\n```\n\nIs enough to handle this? Is there any reason to not always do fsync first? (i.e., perf penalties or undesirable side effects)\n"
