    "updated_at": "2013-10-28T21:32:07Z",
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "I think it best to avoid fsync unless the user requests it, as there are scenarios where they might want to flush, close, and rapidly re-open without a fsync (eg a user relying on thread synchronisation in a single process to achieve a single writer at a time, as in that case the shared OS buffer would be reliable without fsync but it would still be necessary to flush, close and re-open as quickly as possible).\n\nI'll make a PR later today.\n"
